# =============================================================================
# hh_client — Facebook (Meta)'s "Hack type checker client" — the
#              user-facing CLI for the HACK programming language,
#              a statically-typed PHP dialect developed at
#              Facebook starting 2013 as a strict-types fork of
#              PHP for safer large-scale web codebases.  Hack:
#                - Runs on HHVM (HipHop Virtual Machine) — a
#                  high-performance JIT for PHP/Hack
#                - Adds STRICT STATIC TYPING with generics,
#                  enums, type aliases, nullable types
#                - Adds ASYNC/AWAIT via continuations
#                - Adds COLLECTIONS (Vector, Map, Set, Pair,
#                  ImmVector, ImmMap, ImmSet) with literal
#                  syntax distinct from arrays
#                - Adds XHP (XML-like syntax for HTML
#                  templating)
#                - Adds LAMBDAS via the ==> arrow + auto-capture
#                  closures
#                - Adds SHAPES (struct-like with typed fields)
#                - Adds PIPE OPERATOR (|>) for function chaining
#              hh_client is the COMMAND-LINE TYPE CHECKER that
#              talks to a long-running hh_server background
#              daemon for incremental type-checking of a Hack
#              codebase.  Workflow:
#                hh_client start            # start type-check daemon
#                hh_client check            # report current errors
#                hh_client lsp              # talk to editor via LSP
#                hh_client stop             # shutdown daemon
#              Used at Meta-scale on the Facebook codebase (one
#              of the largest Hack monorepos in existence) plus
#              by Slack, Box.com, and several enterprise PHP
#              shops that adopted Hack for type safety.
#
# Author:  Facebook / Meta Hack team — language designed by
#          Julien Verlaguet + Alok Menghrajani + Drew Paroski +
#          Sara Golemon + many Meta engineers since 2013.
#          Hack continues active development at Meta with
#          quarterly releases; the open-source repo at
#          facebook/hhvm hosts both HHVM (the runtime) and
#          the Hack type checker / language server.
# Source:  https://github.com/facebook/hhvm
#          https://github.com/facebook/hhvm/blob/master/hphp/hack/src/client/clientArgs.ml
# CLI:     hphp/hack/src/client/clientArgs.ml — written in
#          OCAML (the Hack type checker + language server is
#          OCaml-implemented; the Hack RUNTIME is C++ HHVM).
#          Uses OCaml stdlib's `Arg` module via
#          `Arg.parse (Arg.align options) anon_fn usage_string`.
# Library: OCaml stdlib Arg module
#          ("The Arg module — Parsing of command line arguments"
#           — OCaml standard library since the 1990s.  Provides
#           `Arg.parse` for triple-tuple argument specifications
#           `(flag, spec, doc)` where `spec` is one of:
#           Arg.Unit fn (boolean flag), Arg.Bool, Arg.Set, Arg.
